latestPosts.caption:
Do you want your hair to look like this?

Stretching natural hair, hair volume, hair density, thick hair, textured hair

@babyliss 

Remember to use heat protectant when applying your products on damp hair. HEAT IS HEAT! Don’t get heat damage 

As you can see I don’t do crazy stretches, it’s mainly to break the gel cast at the roots to give volume and movement to my hair and it adds drama! 

Stretching from the roots and a little bit down the hair shaft also don’t weaken the oldest part of your hair which is your ends. New growth is from the roots. 

Please don’t stretch all the time because heat is still heat! 

#stretchedhair #naturalhair #curlyafro #hair #curlyhairstyles #curlyhair #naturalhair #protectivehairstyle #longnaturalhair #texturedhair #elongatedcurls #coilyhaircare #afrohairstyle #hairdryer #blowdry #babyliss

The most perfect day - Turns out I can have it all

Outfit everything @hm 
Sunglasses @gucci 

1. The outfit - Parisian ballet off duty is the feeling I went for for a little family day out and it is day 2 of discovering my style again after spending over a year pretty much living in my pyjamas as a first time mama!

2. The most perfect day started off with me having time to style my hair after washing it the previous day. I also hacked a few inches off to make my hair look fuller after postpartum hair loss messed with my hair density!

3. The fuller… that cut I did brought new life to my hair don’t you think? Of course we had to stop by the elephant. Baby boy is obsessed with animals, cars and footballs. 

4. History was my favourite subject in school yet I didn’t pass it…clearly I was only interested in the gossip and not the facts. 

5. I’m learning up north they trust people far too easily. Firstly shopping trolleys are free and now beautiful flowers dried and freshly cut are just left out long after the shops clothes. Giving my ideas to have a dried flowers bouquet for my wedding

6. Brit-ish tourist 

7. We took this little one to the library, he was less interested in the books and more interested people watching..like he wasn’t already my son.

8. My boys but also why is our son so sarcastic already look at the pose ha-ha god love him

9. We all had pasta for dinner… so yummy

10. The most beautiful flower shop..I truly felt like I was on holiday

11 & 12. More photos of happy me and the outfit. Notice I swapped between my ballet shoes and flip flops? 

13. He wanted to drive us home but good thing we put him back in his car seat as he fell asleep in the car which was around 7:30pm, I transferred him to his bed when we got him and he slept all the way until 7:13am this morning without even a peep on the monitor. My boobs were bursting as he last feed at 13:30!

latestPosts.caption:
ONE✨

Your birthday, I mean heck your birthday month has come and gone but in all honesty I don’t think there is enough words to articulate how much I truly and unconditionally love you. 

You have given my life, my existence so much purpose. You made me a mother. You took your time to utter the words “mama” but your timing was perfection. 

Months of hearing “Dada dada” and you chose your birthday (my birthing day) to call me “mama”. 

I was casually filming you enjoying your birthday presents and it took me a few seconds to register that you were saying “Mama” and of course I cried. I will never forget it. 

Crying is a constant thing for me now. Not because I’m sad but because I’m so happy and filled with so much love for you that sometimes that love pours out of me in tears.

You are so loved Oliver. I have spent all day every single day with you since birth and you have taught me so much. So much patience. To be in the present, to find joy in the simple things. Watching you discover new things, tastes, smells, textures and sounds. 

You are my wonder and magic.

You are curious, loving, funny, super cheeky, speedy, busy, smart, full of understanding, adventurous, daring, a leader, determined and mostly and importantly you are so kind, there is nothing you wouldn’t share.

Thank you for choosing me to be your mummy. Your Dad and I love you so much. You made us a family. You are literally my heart. You are the very best parts of both of us. We are so proud of you always and forever. Thank God for blessing us with the soul, spirit and presence that you embody. 

My wish for you always and forever is good health, happiness and safety and the rest you will carve out for yourself! 

I will always do my very best by you and for you. 

#ourson #one #birthday #firsts

latestPosts.caption:
ad 🐑💤👶🏽 Ewan Deluxe arrived 

With new and improved removable control pod – that’s fully rechargeable via the USB control pod

10 sleep inducing sounds and offers continuous playback

3 different timer playback options - 20, 40 and 80 minutes

SmartCRY function cleverly listens out, automatically activating if a baby stirs. Switches off after 4 hours to help conserve battery life

So, the morning after I had a terrible night sleep with my little one I thought this was a sure sign this will be the answer to my dreams…see what I did there?!

I have shared before my son’s sleep was a big thing for me in the early stages. Although not perfect it is something that rarely bothers me these days except for when it seems like we are in a regression.

Bare in mind I got this when he was 11 months and we have established a sleep routine already and even if not perfect, it works for us and I think his one/two wake up at night is due to me continuing to breastfeed. 

I did try Ewan to see if it will prevent his wake up but this introduction to Ewan so late only distracted him from sleeping as he was curious about the glow and sound coming from it. 

However I did remove the pod and attached Ewan by its tail at the bottom of his cot which he likes when he wakes to have something to entertain him and it stops him screaming to alert me that he’s awake.

I will keep it for when I hopefully have a second baby and introduce it them then from the womb because I am hoping I don’t have the sleep start that I did with my son.

#ewanthedreamsheep #ewandeluxe #babysleeproutine #babysleeping #babysleephelp #babysleeptips #babysleep #babysleepsupport

latestPosts.caption:
ad 💤 I wish I knew this from the new born stage to now 

Safer sleep week 
By @lullabytrust runs from 10th-16th March 

I remember in the early stages leaving my nct group chat because it seemed like I was the only one struggling with my child’s sleep and therefore feeling like I’m failing. 

As a first time mum I don’t think I considered or looked into what a baby’s sleep cycle would look like other than what I know, was, considered safe sleep.

But I figured once a baby is safely in their bed, on their back, with cellular blanket, not covering shoulder and feet at the base of the crib/cot/moses basket and nothing else in the cot that’s it, the baby would sleep maybe not long at first but they sleep and pretty soon through the night… right? 

Wrong…of course every baby’s sleep is different. My son however loved sleeping anywhere I was and I mean he wanted to be as close to be as possible, contact sleeping, sling sleeping, co sleeping that was his preference.

His idea of a prefect sleep and mine did not match. 

It didn’t help that no one was sharing what a realistic sleep cycle looked like with a breastfeeding baby.

Breastfeeding baby is more prone to waking. Breastfeeding babies are happiest by mum (not all) but I was trying to stick to what I was told how to safely sleep.

I wish I knew cosleeping was common and if you have to do it for rest and sanity there’s guidelines how to safely do so. 

Also it’s not uncommon to be a year in and your baby isn’t sleeping through the night. 

From someone who tried it all, next to me, cosleeping, sling sleeping, leaving him to sleep in his carry cot, leaving him to sleep in his rocker, letting him sleep in his sleep nest, buying Moses basket, swaddles nothing seemed to work for long periods. 

We finally settled on cosleeping which worked for us and we did so safely. He now sleeps in his cot in his own room and at most only wakes twice but sometimes just the once a night. He can sleep through the night if we cosleep which happens on occasion if he gets poorly or if his day routine goes out the window. 

Remember no matter how tired you are, always practice safe sleeping. #safersleepweek #babysleeptips #babysleep
